<br>
I'm starting to wonder whether the last quarter of the 21st century isn't one big assed experiment where, at least in western industrialized countries, the supreme being says &quot;Let's see how we can fuck with these humans and see how they react to being overworked, overstressed, etc.&quot; <br>
<br>
How do we or did we react? Gravitate towards politicians without substance, media stimulation that went from reasoned discourse like William Buckley or Phil Donohue to Jerry Springer\Jenny Jones? Families that cracked at the foundation level? While all along people themselves are still objectively just trying to make do and get along from one paycheck to the next. <br>
<br>
Maybe at some level-- life and public discourse is shallower because the body politik has been squashed by circumstance....splat!!! Of course that sounds like the mantra of victim. The real failing was with institutions not being able to support people under the weight of what has happened over the last 40 years. <br>
<br>
People who craft institutions or policies that support institutions in the broader sense of that word seldom are forward thinkers. The next election or next fiscal quarter report is far more centerstage for that type.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fadorib>Fadori B</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/14/02 3:00:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1824.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stupid People and Customer Service</span><hr size=1> I fix metalworking machines, and provide phone support for both customers and coworkers, as well as field service.  My area is basically Washington, Oregon, Idaho, and southern BC, but I live in the Seattle area.  So one day I get a call from our FNG (Fucking New Guy for those who don't know the phrase)  He's our latest and greatest Oregon guy, and is going to load software on a machine.  He's been at this 20+ years, and is a very smurt guy (so I'm told)  So I go through the backup procedure with him, then the install procedure, then the restore procedure.  I tell him to go ahead and do it and call me if he has ANY questions . . . so he backs it up, loads software, then backs up again over his backup.  Of course he doesn't call me or anything, calls my boss and tells him I made a mistake in the procedure I gave him, and thus my boss sends me to go fix it.  Keep in mind, it's after noon so my shift is almost over, and the customer is 6 hours away from me, so I tell my boss ok I'll head down first thing in the morning.  <br>
<br>
That isn't good enough, go there now and fix it, then head back etc etc.  So I drive, and drive, and drive.  I get there, and instead of staying to learn what the fuck he did wrong he heads home, so I call him.  He turned off his cell and wouldn't answer his home phone (damn I wish I could get outta things that easy when I fuck up)  The customer is a good friend of mine, and had been watching my fellow coworker fuck up, had even told him he was making a mistake but no he wouldn't listen . . .<br>
<br>
So anyways, some time in the early morning we get done and I start home, after having a fun night of doing a full system restore.  By 8 AM I'm an hour away from home and my boss is just getting in to work, so I call her.  I explain how he'd fucked up and what I'd done, and I'm headed home to get some much needed sleep, but no, she has another day's worth of work already scheduled and I can either come back to work or not come back, since it was all MY fault the Oregon customer had a problem.<br>
<br>
Now since then, this guy's broken several other machines that I've had to go fix, and just received the highest award at the company christmas party for dedication to the company and all his hard work.  Just thought I'd share, the idiots aren't always on the customer side &gt;&lt;<br>
<br>
And btw, no I don't work for Verant, although I think they'd hire this guy in a heartbeat <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cerosofvazaelle>Ceros of Vazaelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 1091<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/14/02 8:44:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1824.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stupid People and Customer Service</span><hr size=1> Yeah, incompetence is everywhere, not just by customers.  In the end, we're all customers anyway. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I somewhat agree with Goanad, I think a large part of the problem is that people are over-worked and over-stressed which is absurd given the technological acheivements or society develops.  Unfortunately, technology offers most people trivia and while they work more and deal with a toxic environment as part of every day life, the top end of companies and professionals reap true benefits from the advancements of our society and take a larger percentage of a pie than they ever have.  It used to be the average man could have a family, home and car off a middle-class pay check, now a family needs two middle-class pay checks while living in vast debt for most of their lives, and might eventually own their own home.<br>
